    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-11T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <head>96. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Cuba</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d96fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 737.00/7–1158. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_NIACT1"
                        >Niact</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-11T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1958—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. During my exchange of views with <persName corresp="#p_BZF1"
                        >Batista</persName> on July 10, he stated that if the overthrow of the
                        <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> were brought about by US intervention,
                    as described in <gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 49,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d96fn2">
                        <ref target="#d94">Document 94</ref>.</note> only chaos and a complete
                    breakdown of law and order would ensue in Cuba.</p>
                <p>These are the conditions the Communists are striving for.</p>
                <p>He further stated that <persName corresp="#p_CRR1">Raul Castro</persName> spent
                    three years behind the Iron Curtain and obviously has been fully
                    indoctrinated.</p>
                <p>I stressed the fact that the US had no such intentions and that we appreciated
                    the support of the friendly <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> as often
                    displayed in all international matters. I further stated that I would make
                    inquiries regarding the allegations in <gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss>
                    49.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEET1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
